<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-584] produce/fetch remote time metric not set correctly when num.acks = 1</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-584</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When num.acks = 1, the produce/fetch remote time is set to a very high value (several hours). This is due to a race condition on the apiLocalTime, which is initialized to -1, that makes the (responseTime - apiLocalTime) a very large value.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12613415">KAFKA-584</key>
            <summary>produce/fetch remote time metric not set correctly when num.acks = 1</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
